Lender Summary 

DreamSpring is a nonprofit community lender dedicated to eliminating systemic wealth inequities and accelerating the economic inclusion and strength of underserved communities. Founded in 1994, the organization, which operates in 19 states, provides rapid access to capital and customized wrap-around support to the most vulnerable small business owners, focusing on communities including people of color, women, low- to moderate-income earners, people with disabilities, and start-ups. DreamSpring has issued more than 42,000 loans totaling over $465 million to small businesses that have supported over 72,000 jobs. Pros: Flexible, personalized service, fast, fixed rate products.
